# Netlify _redirects — SPA fallback.
# Flutter web uses hash routing by default (#/auth/phone), so SPA fallback
# isn't strictly required, but pasting a deep link or refreshing on a
# sub-route otherwise 404s. The catch-all rewrites any unknown path to
# index.html with a 200 so the Flutter router takes over client-side.
#
# Static files (assets/, icons/, canvaskit/, *.js, *.json, *.png, etc.) are
# served as files because Netlify checks the literal path before applying
# the rewrite — only paths that don't match a real file fall through here.

/*    /index.html   200
